The story of the McMartin Pre-School molestation case appears headed for television and  the bookstores.
Screenwriter and producer Abby Mann became interested in the theme-- the hysteria of a witch hunt--in 1986 and allied with both the prosecution and the defense.
He and his wife have a manuscript and screenplay in the works.
Two other books are  planned.
Others also see "movie of the week" potential.
The networks, however, may  not be willing to run the lurid tale because of ambiguities created by the jury's deadlock  on 13 of the charges.
Child abuse and molestation already have become a more visible  Hollywood theme. 
